RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligib ility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUBA'S HOUSE chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path, left the turn outside then lugged in through the stretch and got up the final strides. ALL WORKED UP was hustled clear and angled to the inside to set a pressured pace, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn but was caught in the final strides. CHURCH KEY chased inside and raced near the rail on the turn, eased out leaving the turn, steadied lightly mid-stretch and was shuffled back from between the top two in late yards. BESTLA chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, altered course toward the outside mid-stretch and finished strong. RISKSRHIGHPAYISLOW gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. REVEIRS MINUTE chased through the backstretch, raced in the two and three paths of the turn then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. MODELO RUBIA saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Juba's House
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,4p turn,outside 1/8,lugged in lane,up final strides

ENTRY.NAME: All Worked Up
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled clear,set pace inside,rail turn,caught final strides

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 42. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN SALLY rated a slim lead inside, dueled Weavinyouinthedust from the three eighths pole and drew clear of that one toward the five sixteenths, was met by JUJU ON DA BEAT and dueled at mostly even terms nearest the rail, dug in determinedly leaving the turn and kept a head in front. The latter was rated close inside on the first turn, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole, contested even terms two deep on the far turn and dug in gamely to the wire. SUNSET QUEEN settled off the rail on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced two deep on the far turn, then flattened in the lane. BANK CARD saved ground off the pace, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, was steadied in tight at the rail midway on the far turn but came back to finish evenly. AFLEET PENGUIN rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but flattened in the four path of the far turn. WEAVINYOUINTHEDUST raced with the pace two deep, dueled leaving the three eighths pole but dropped back toward the five sixteenths and weakened on the far turn. XALTINGRUN rounded the opening turn about the four path and never factored. The Stewards reviewed and dismissed a claim of foul against the rider of Sunset Queen for alleged interference on the far turn, lodged by the rider of Bank Card.

ENTRY.NAME: Bank Card
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved early ground,bid 7/16,steadied rail mid turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Juju On Da Beat
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,bid 3/8,even terms 2d turn,gamely lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Allowance Purse 35100. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 4 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREAT SPIRIT pressured the pace and contested even terms two deep leaving the quarter pole, dug in determinedly through the stretch and inched ahead of STRYDA through the final yards. The latter set a pressured pace inside, was met at even terms leaving the quarter pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and dug in gamely through the lane, though, reluctantly ceded late yards. KEEP ON SPURRIN gave chase through the backstretch, raced at the rail on the turn and dug in for third nearing mid-stretch. LUCKY BLONDE came away a bit awkwardly and steadied leaving the chute, picked up the chase toward the outside, rounded the turn two deep and ran evenly in the lane. LA MADDALENA chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail but drifted into the lane and flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. MAKINLIMMARGARITAS gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path and showed little in the lane. Lucky Bop ran loose in the post parade and was a late scratch.

ENTRY.NAME: Stryda
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace inside,even terms rail turn,reluctantly ceded

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Blonde
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward break,steadied leaving chute,chased,2d turn,evenly lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 16900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE SEPTEMBER 4, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 126 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAT DARES GOLD settled in the three and four paths the first turn, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced close off the rail on the far turn, dug in leaving the eighth pole and got up in the final yards. SOME IS NINE raced with the early pace inside, drifted outward and made contact with Salty Saul at the nine sixteenths pole and showed the way from that point, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, contested the advantage at the rail on the far turn, was met mid-stretch and relented later yards. MARVELLA NASTY settled in the four path the first turn and gave chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn about the four path and ran evenly in the lane. FLOATING BY saved early ground, started a bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and passed rivals outside. SHINY PENNY saved ground just off the early pace, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail then flattened in the lane. DUSTWHIRL WONDER rounded the first turn about the five path, left the turn outside and showed little response through the backstretch. TORCH CARRIER raced well back off the rail on the first turn, left the turn in mid track and showed little response. SALTY SAUL raced with the early pace two deep, was bumped outward in the vicinity of the nine sixteenths pole, challenged toward the three eighths but faded readily on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Torch Carrier
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back off rail,mid track 1/2,little response

ENTRY.NAME: Floating By
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,5p far turn,passed rivals outside

ENTRY.NAME: Marvella Nasty
ENTRY.OWNER: Bush Racing Stable and Liberty House Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JALEBI BABY took a quick lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on well. IRISH SAMURAI became a bit anxious in the gate and rated close inside on the first turn, started a three wide bid nearing the three eighths pole, contested the far turn still three wide and dueled for a clear second nearing the sixteenth pole. LADY WHISTLEDOWN broke outward and made contact with Fort Zanna then rated close in the three and four paths, bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and came along for third later yards. CHANNEL SCENT steadied early and raced well off the pace inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, angled six wide on the far turn and passed rivals in an even finish. KOBE'S GIRL stalked the pace two deep, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole and contested at a close disadvantage two deep while between horses on the far turn, but flattened inside the eighth pole. FORT ZANNA was bumped outward and into Uptown Belle leaving the gate, raced well back on the opening turn and never factored. PRETTY SPECTACULAR rounded the first turn about the three path, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole then flattened in the four path of the far turn. SHESAHUMBLEHUSTLER was not a factor. ULTIMATE BREEZE raced off the rail on the first turn and showed little response. UPTOWN BELLE was bumped leaving the gate then saved ground on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole but faded into the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Samurai
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: anxious in gate,rated close,3wd bid 3/8,close turn,clear 2nd lane

ENTRY.NAME: Channel Scent
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied early,saved ground,chased 7/16,6wd far turn,even finish

ENTRY.NAME: Jalebi Baby
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 7/16,edge turn,held well driving

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Adrian Regan, Fergus Galvin,Tony Hegarty & John Wade

ENTRY.NAME: Uptown Belle
ENTRY.OWNER: Wilson Rayan and Knoblauch Michelle R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eli gibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ICE BAR saved ground well off the pace, bid leaving the three eighths pole and steadily made his way through traffic to get up the final strides. BOOK OF DELANCEY settled in the three path, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and took the lead two deep approaching the head of the lane, dueled clear leaving the eighth pole but was caught in the final strides. SULEMAN settled off the pace in the three and four paths, left the second turn outside and bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the six path of the far turn and finished well to take third later yards. RIGHTEOUS MAN settled off the rail, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced close in the four path of the far turn, but flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE raced off the pace in the two and three paths, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and showed little in the lane. URBAN WARRIOR rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, was met into the lane and faded. PROUD UNION raced well back and never factored. TYLER TIME rated close inside, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and weakened in the lane. OFFICER APPEAL raced with the pace two deep, challenged toward the seven sixteenths pole then faded off the rail on the far turn. DOHKO settled off the rail and faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Urban Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead,pressured 7/16,edge rail far turn,faded lane

ENTRY.NAME: Ice Bar
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,rail far turn,through traffic lane,up late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 19400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8 ,000 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEST VIRGINIA accelerated to the lead at the three quarter pole and angled in to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the seven sixteenths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, was met into the lane but immediately recovered the advantage and dueled clear later yards. PETTYFORURTHOUGHTS was bumped leaving the gate then rated close inside, challenged approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn, took a brief slim lead entering the stretch but relented past the eighth pole and flattened inside the sixteenth. APPEALING ROAD rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the five path and came along for third later yards. I SHALLBE RELEASED rounded the first turn in the three path, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn in the three path then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. MAY MAYS CASTLE bore in and made contact with Pettyforurthoughts leaving the gate then settled in the three path of the opening turn, bid approaching the three eighths pole, raced close in the three path of the far turn but flattened leaving the eighth pole. ALLI BOBBY rounded the first turn in the four path, challenged nearing the seven sixteenths pole but faded into the far turn. WOODSONG'S CASTLE saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Appealing Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,chased 3/8,5p far turn,along 3rd later yards

ENTRY.NAME: May Mays Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: bore in,bumped break,3p 1st turn,bid 3/8,3p far turn,flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Best Virginia
ENTRY.OWNER: O'Sullivan Farms LLC and Conrad Randall R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 92. Starter Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE MARCH 4, 2021. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 4 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 4 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Enter ed For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DULCIMER DAME settled off the rail on the first turn, closed to a clear lead three wide midway on the far turn and was kept alert to widen. VOLNAY saved ground on the opening turn, bid nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and cleared second mid-stretch. SHERIFF'S KID rounded the first turn about the four path, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and came along for third later yards. FLAT DISCOUNT rated close to the early pace, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole and dueled to a slim brief lead toward the five sixteenths, was caught midway on the far turn and weakened into the lane. CHINA CAT raced off the rail on the opening turn and showed little response through the backstretch. TARGE moved to the inside and set the early pace, came under pressure nearing the seven sixteenths pole, was caught approaching the five sixteenths and weakened on the far turn. SAX and TEMPORARILY were not factors. MALIBU MARLEE was taken up early and only galloped around.

ENTRY.NAME: Dulcimer Dame
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,clear 3wd mid turn,kept alert to widen

ENTRY.NAME: Sheriff's Kid
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st turn,chased 3/8,off rail far turn,along 3rd later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 9 7F Dirt CR: 48. Maiden Claiming Purse 13300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DULINI rounded the opening turn in the five path, started a bid into the backstretch and steadily progressed from that point, rounded the far turn near the rail, got up for the lead between horses mid-stretch and held on well. WHY LEA rounded the first turn in the four path, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole and raced close in the three path on the far turn, dueled through the stretch and took second late yards. SHADES OF BLUE rated off the early pace about the three path, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, contested at a close disadvantage off the rail on the far turn then outfinished for second in late yards. I'M SO EXTRA tapered in and took over at the three quarter pole and rated the pace, came under pressure approaching the five sixteenths, rounded the far turn at the rail, was met mid-stretch and weakened the final sixteenth. CAN'T FIGURE became extremely fractious and sat in the gate, rounded the opening turn in the four and five paths and gave chase leaving the half mile pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. REGGAETONI saved ground racing well back, eased out into the backstretch and gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the six and seven paths and passed rivals outside. UNBRIDLED IRISH raced off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole then flattened off the rail on the far turn. DAPPLESANDDIAMONDS rounded the first turn in the six path, left the turn outside and showed little response. MAKO MISS stalked the early pace inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. JO AMY became extremely fractious and sat in the gate, raced in the three path the first turn, never factored and was eased leaving the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Reggaetoni
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,6& 7p far turn,passed rval

ENTRY.NAME: Jo Amy
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious,sat in gate,off pace 3p 1st turn,no factor,eased lane

ENTRY.NAME: Why Lea
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st turn,bid 3/8,3p far turn,dug in lane,up 2nd late
